// Data types and keywords in java

// A type identifies a set of values (and their representation in the memory) and a set of operations that transform these values into other vales of set.
// Java is strongly typed language.

// Primitive datatype
// User define datatype

// Primitive datatype                    Size
// (1) Boolean                          implementation dependent
// (2) Char                             16 bits (syore unicode)
// (3) Bytes                            8 bits
// (4) Short                            16 bits
// (5) Int                              32 bits
// (6) Long                             64 bits
// (7) Float                            32 bits
// (8) Double                           64 bits

// Constants
// integer constant consists of a sequence of digits
// if the consists is to represent a long integer value, it must be suffixed with an upper case L or lower case I
// If there is no suffix the constant represnets 32 bits integer.
// integer constant can be specified in the decimal,hexadecimal,octa or binary format.
